description:
Job Description


Delivering social media campaigns through social media platforms: Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter, LINE, Wechat etc.;
Planning and executing online advertising strategies of various platforms;
Maintain daily operations for the social media advertising campaigns including content creation, posting, ad placing and monitoring;
Closely monitor and analyze the social media advertising performance and its return of investment;
Formulate insightful strategies and creative ideas to meet clients’ objectives, ensure successful execution, flow and end-result;
Maintain relationship with new and existing customers;
Perform any ad-hoc duties as assigned.
The Successful Applicant


Bachelor’s degree in Marketing Communication or related;
Minimum 3 year practical experience in social media platforms, agency experience preferred;
Understanding on social media trends and best practices across the digital and new media sectors;
Ability to lead and motivate a team to deliver results;
Eager to learn, cheerful, detail-oriented and polite;
Proficiency in MS Office applications e.g. Word, Excel etc.
media sectors;
Good written and spoken English & Chinese;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Digital Performance Manager.
What's On Offer


5-day work
Bank Holidays and other special leave (e.g. Birthday Leave, Family Leave, etc...)
Medical Insurance
Team Building Activities
Digital Marketing Training will be provided
Friendly Work Environment
Interest parties please send your CV with availability, current and expected salary to us.
**Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only**

Job Description


Manage key accounts in a timely and professional manner;
Provide strategic media advice and guidance to ensure clients’ objectives are met;
Manage campaigns deliverable and coordinate with project team, creative team, digital team and operational team to implement the best class of digital marketing;
Closely monitor and analyze advertising performance, drive recommendations and action plans;
Prepare pitching proposals, quotations and presentations;
Prepare reports and attend review meetings for project optimization and explore further cooperation opportunities with clients.
The Successful Applicant


Degree holder majoring in Communications, Marketing, Journalism, PR, Arts, or related disciplines is an advantage;
Minimum 1 year of relevant account servicing and/or in-house marketing experience, preferably in social media, digital marketing, or public relations industries;
Excellent communications and writing skills in Cantonese and English; Mandarin is a plus;
Good organization, project management, and interpersonal skills;
Familiar with digital marketing and advertising e.g. Google, Facebook, LinkedIn, WeChat, Line, TV, video production etc;
Immediate availability is preferred.
What's On Offer


5-day work
Bank Holidays and other special leave (e.g. Birthday Leave, Family Leave, etc...)
Medical Insurance
Staff Training
Team Building Activities
Friendly Work Environment
Interest parties please send your CV with availability, current and expected salary to us.
**Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only**

Job Responsibilities

Understand clients’ needs and deliver creative and innovative business solutions;
Sharp creative mind, collaborate with Account Management team to pitching/developing new ideas to clients
Identify market opportunities and potential strategic partnerships to capture new business and to expand market share
Contribute to the development of projects and responsible for researching, planning, executing, and preparing creative briefs in line with project needs & goals
Elevate the creative concept, design, and execution of various formats of contents
Assist in developing overall corporate branding and marketing strategy

Job Requirements

Bachelor’s degree on Marketing, Multimedia,, Communications, or related disciplines;
At least 1 years’ experience in digital marketing agency
Excellent command in Cantonese, English and Mandarin ;
Proficient in MS PowerPoint and Excel;
Multimedia experience is preferred;
Excellent communication and analytical skills;
Corporately presentable and business savvy
Able to work under pressure and tight deadlines;
Excellent attention to detail, work independently, flexible and willing to learn;

Requirements:

Bachelor degree in Advertising, Mass Communication, Marketing or related disciplines;
1 - 2 year of relevant work experience with proven capabilities of being strategic and creative in handling digital marketing campaigns;
 A natural user of social media and forums as well as natural player of mobile games
 Passionate and familiar with various online media platforms;
Good marketing sense, multi-tasking and good management;
Presentable, independent, proactive and creative;
 A good team player, able and flexible to work with people of different cultures;

Responsibilities:

- Help develop integrated digital marketing solutions for clients, including but not limited to social  media maintenance, creative campaign, video campaign, website production, O2O solution, media  placement, Social CRM, etc.

- Formulate insightful strategies and creative ideas to meet clients’ objectives, ensure successful  execution, flow and end-result.

- Prepare documents to pitch clients, e.g. marketing plan, schedule, budget etc.;

- Present ideas to clients together with the Project Management Team, if necessary;

- Explore and assimilate the latest digital marketing trends and develop knowledge management    database for internal and external training

- Assist in key client project management and coordinate communication with both internal and  external parties.

We offer performance bonus, medical coverage, bank holidays, and wedding leaves to right candidates. Interested parties please send a cover letter stating your expected salary, resume and a full set of your portfolio to Mr. Yeung. 

*All information will be treated as confidential and used solely for recruitment purposes.

Job Description:

Assist manager to prepare and execute digital advertising campaigns;
Work closely with vendors and internal teams to plan, develop and execute digital marketing projects;
Meet and liaise with clients to ensure client satisfaction;
Coordinate with art directors and social media editors to develop social media contents; 
Responsible for committed timelines and deliverable throughout projects;
Prepare advertising plans for search, display, video and social media ads;
Other ad-hoc assignments.


Requirements:

Strong Responsibility in handling projects; 
Have experience in managing one or more of below digital marketing channels is preferred: Facebook, Instagram, KOL, micro influencer, video production, Google Adwords or Forum;
1 - 3 years working experience in an agency or in a marketing position;
Good project management and communication skill;
Attention to details and ability to work under tight timeline and multi-task independently;
Knowledge in video or photo editing is a plus.

Benefits:

Five-day work week
Birthday Leave
Bank holidays
Shuttle Bus to/from work

Location: Kwai Chung

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

