instructions
1. Responsible for sales team building in Hong Kong company;
2. Network with exchanges and investment managers and analysts at well-known investment banks such as Morgan Stanley, CICC, Goldman Sachs, etc.
3. Responsible for introducing and promoting Capitalwatch media platform to customers, and conducting investor relations and public relations related inquiries for Chinese listed companies in Hong Kong;
4. Responsible for developing and providing services to clients of Chinese companies planning to or already listed in Hong Kong.

requirements
1. Bachelor degree or above, major in finance, economics or management;
2. Experience in advertising investor relations of Hong Kong listed companies, or investing in Chinese listed companies in Hong Kong: public relations companies, traditional media, enterprises and other fields;
3, have sales experience (provide cases);
4. Resources of listed companies are preferred

Responsibility:

Handle multiple client projects such as video production, influencer activation, social media management, and other digital marketing campaigns;
Provide creative inputs in social media content and campaign planning;
Manage timeline to ensure smooth project execution;
Prepare proposals and support new clients pitching;
Liaise with and provide creative briefings to vendors, designers, internal and external parties;
Monitor project implementation and performance against KPIs;
Compile regular and post-campaign reports for project performance evaluations;
Stay alert to industry happenings and able to share insights; 

Requirement: 

Degree in Media, Marketing, Communications or related discipline;
Minimum 1 year experience on digital/social media management or other relevant work experience;
Demonstrate strong communication and presentation skills;
Familiar with the social media & influencer landscape and practices in Hong Kong; 
Proficiency in written and spoken English and Chinese; 
Proactive, passionate, and a detail-minded team player;
Good multi-tasking skills, willing to work under pressure and tight schedules;
Experience working with social listening and social media management tools is a plus;  
Immediate availability is highly preferred;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Account Executive;

All personal data collected will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Responsibilities:
Develop and execute both offline/ digital marketing and social media strategies and plans including the implementation of digital initiatives in website, social media, SEO/ SEM, EDM and other digital platform to achieve aggressive business growth and digital acquisition objectives;
Manage website, on-line shop, crowdfunding, devise digital marketing and social media strategies to raise brand awareness, generate sales leads and engage customers for Hong Kong and Global Market; 
Establish digital brand presence, digital CRM program, drive traffic and brand visibility in online marketing platform and social media to drive customer engagement;
Evaluate effectiveness of digital marketing campaigns with performance/ analysis reports (google/digital analytics, social media/competitive research and web behavior analysis) with targeting to maximize ROI of various marketing activities and to achieve KPI;
Develop marketing materials for content marketing/ online promotion/ digital campaign and Pop-up store;
Utilize a range of techniques including paid search SEO/ SEM, website development and social media management to meet business objectives;
Continuously review new technologies and keep the brand at the forefront of developments in digital marketing;
Ongoing provide marketing insights and explore opportunities to cope with business growth;
Own social influencer (celebrity / KOL / micro influencer) strategies;
Assist in ad-hoc marketing project.
Job Requirements:
Bachelor Degree holder or above in Communication, Marketing, e-Commerce, Brand Management, Business Administration or other related discipline is preferred;
Minimum 8 years relevant experience in in digital marketing experience/eCommerce, and brand management capacity,
Proven experience in managing and driving website development and executing digital campaigns;
Experience in consumer electronics goods, IoT home appliance goods & retail products is advantage;
Strong in search engine optimization (SEO) with proven result and experience in manage crowdfunding & online shop is essential;
Keep updating the knowledge of digital marketing related technologies, tactics and practices;
Pro-active, dynamic and self-disciplined with positive attitude;
Strong business acumen and innovative thinking, result-oriented, good team player;
Good analytical and presentation skills;
Proficiency in both written & spoken English and Chinese (Cantonese & Mandarin);
Immediate available is definitely an advantage;
Less experience will be considered as Senior Marketing Manager.
Interested parties, please send us an email to obtain an application form.


All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.
Interested candidates, please contact us at 94534547 for company details before applying.

